name: Beau DeMayo
summary: Marvel has fired Beau DeMayo, the creator of the upcoming animated series "X-Men '97," for "egregious misconduct." DeMayo alleges that Disney removed his credit from the second season due to a post he made in support of Pride Month. Marvel claims that the investigation into DeMayo's conduct found egregious findings and that his firing had nothing to do with his Pride post. DeMayo's lawyer has accused Disney of "gaslighting" and hinted at possible legal action. Marvel has strongly denied these allegations and says the decision to remove DeMayo's credit was made before his Pride post. DeMayo has since released a pitch for a Wesley Snipes Blade film.

summary: News articles featuring Representative Nancy Mace have sparked controversy due to her repeated mispronunciation of Vice President Kamala Harris' name. These articles have garnered attention and criticism, with critics accusing Mace of intentional disrespect or bias.
